<h1>Hints on exercise 5</h1>

<h3>If you intend to use PL/SQL, you may find the following
link helpful:
<a href="http://www.orafaq.org/faqplsql.htm">
http://www.orafaq.org/faqplsql.htm</a>

<br><br>
Generic Documentation on Oracle 8i can be found at:
        file:/usr/local/share/oracle/product/8.1.5/doc/index.htm

<br><br>
In the following Oracle help site, you may find Oracle 8 on Unix
and Connect with JDBC in Oracle8 very useful.

<a href="http://www2.cs.pitt.edu/~panos/teaching/d1555.02/system_docs/system_docs.html"> 
http://www2.cs.pitt.edu/~panos/teaching/d1555.02/system_docs/system_docs.html 
</a>

<br><br>
The following are further hints if you intend to use Excel and Oracle to do the exercise:

<br>
<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'>1. Please read: <a
href="http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/156/06oracle/myexample.html">http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/156/06oracle/myexample.html</a><br>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">                       </span><a
href="http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/156/06oracle/getname.html">http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/156/06oracle/getname.html</a>
<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">                       </span><a
href="http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/156/06oracle/retreive.html">http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~chang/156/06oracle/retreive.html</a>
<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">   
</span>These documents are enough for you to do the exercise using Excel and Oracle.

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'>2. The following Module is <span
style='color:maroon'>STRICTLY REQUIRED</span>:

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">                               </span>Sub Auto_Open()<o:p></o:p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">              </span><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">                                </span>UserForm1.Show<o:p></o:p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">       </span><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">                        </span>End Sub

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">   
</span>If your program works well, this module should bring the interface out
as you open the file (*.xls).<o:p></o:p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none'>3. Table Name and Field Name are <span style='color:maroon'>STRICTLY
REQUIRED</span> to be exactly the following: <span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>STUDENT, NAME,
SSN, MOD, COMPLETE_DATE, GRADE (some of them<br>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">    </span>should be needed in the program),
because your program would be tested on the database that I give. I are not
responsible for modifying your code to match my STUDENT table.<o:p></o:p></span>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>4: You are NOT
allowed to modify these two sentences:<o:p></o:p></span>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">    </span>Set OraSession =
CreateObject(&quot;OracleInProcServer.XOraSession&quot;)<o:p></o:p></span>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">   </span><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">    </span>Set OraDatabase = OraSession.OpenDatabase(&quot;<b><i><span
style='color:maroon'>beq-local.world</span></i></b>&quot;, &quot;<b><i><span
style='color:maroon'>scott/tiger</span></i></b>&quot;, 0&amp;)<o:p></o:p></span>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>5. When you close
your file or EXCEL, maybe you would run into this problem:<o:p></o:p></span>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:120%;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none'><span style='color:black'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">     </span></span><i><span style='color:maroon'>The Macros in This
Project Are Disabled<o:p></o:p></span></i>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:3.0pt;line-height:120%;mso-layout-grid-align:
none;text-autospace:none'><span style='color:black'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">    </span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span>Solution to this
problem:<o:p></o:p></span>

<ol style='margin-top:0in' start=1 type=1>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;line-height:120%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>Close your
     file if it is still open.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;line-height:120%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>On the <b>Tools</b>
     menu, point to <b>Macro</b> and click <b>Security</b>.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;line-height:120%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>In the <b>Security</b>
     dialog box, click the Security Level tab.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;line-height:120%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>Click <b>Medium</b>
     and then click <b>OK</b>.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='color:black;line-height:120%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;
     tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt'>As you open your
     file(*.xls), when prompted whether to enable or disable macros, click <b>Enable
     Macros.</b><o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ol>

